      "content": "It's completely understandable to feel that professional help might feel insufficient when your pain is this immense. The feeling that life is pointless is a very heavy burden, and that level of exhaustion is real. Even small things—like having a cup of tea in the sun or listening to a piece of music—can sometimes offer tiny moments of grounding. If the overwhelming feeling becomes too much, please consider reaching out to a crisis hotline for immediate, non-judgmental support.",
      "source": "target",
